import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['rate'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the overall distribution of unemployment rates?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['id'] = data['id'].astype(str)
    data = data.sort_values(by='rate', ascending=False)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.subplot(111)
    ax.bar(data['id'], data['rate'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Which location has the highest unemployment rate?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Location ID')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['id'] = data['id'].astype(str)
    data = data.groupby('id').mean()
    plt.bar(data.index, data['rate'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average unemployment rate by location?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['id'], data['rate'])
    plt.xlabel('Location Size')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between location size and unemployment rate?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['id'] = data['id'].astype(str)
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['rate'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the trend of unemployment rates over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
